---
import SplitLayout from '../layouts/SplitLayout.astro';
const title = "Kindle Jailbreak Guide";
---

<SplitLayout title={title}>
  <h2>Kindle Jailbreak Guide</h2>
  <p>The Amazon Kindle is one of the most popular e-readers worldwide, but it has limitations like restricted file formats, no third-party apps, and limited customization.</p>

  <h3>Supported Kindle Models</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Kindle Paperwhite (1st to latest generation)</li>
    <li>Kindle Oasis (all versions)</li>
    <li>Kindle Basic (various models)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Why Jailbreak Your Kindle?</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Install custom reading apps such as KOReader for advanced features</li>
    <li>Customize fonts, margins, and UI themes beyond Amazon’s defaults</li>
    <li>Read unsupported e-book formats (ePub, etc.)</li>
    <li>Access enhanced annotations and note-taking features</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Step-by-Step Jailbreak Process</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Check your Kindle firmware:</strong> Go to <em>Settings &gt; Device Info</em> and note the firmware version exactly (e.g., 5.13.7).</li>
    <li><strong>Download the jailbreak file:</strong> Visit the official community repo to find the correct jailbreak for your firmware version:
      <br />
      <a href="https://github.com/geek1011/kindle-jailbreak" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://github.com/geek1011/kindle-jailbreak</a>
      <br />Download the <code>jailbreak.bin</code> file matching your Kindle firmware.
    </li>
    <li><strong>Connect your Kindle to your PC:</strong> Use a USB cable to connect. Your Kindle should appear as a USB drive.</li>
    <li><strong>Copy the jailbreak file:</strong> Place the <code>jailbreak.bin</code> file in the root directory of your Kindle (do not put it inside any folder).</li>
    <li><strong>Eject and disconnect your Kindle:</strong> Safely eject the device from your computer and unplug the USB cable.</li>
    <li><strong>Start the jailbreak:</strong> On your Kindle, go to <em>Settings &gt; Device Options &gt; Advanced Options</em> and select <em>Update Your Kindle</em>. Confirm when prompted.</li>
    <li><strong>Wait for the process to complete:</strong> Your Kindle will reboot and apply the jailbreak automatically. Do not turn it off or unplug during this.</li>
    <li><strong>Verify the jailbreak:</strong> Look for the new “Enable Jb” app on your Home screen. Open it and follow any final instructions.</li>
    <li><strong>Install KOReader (optional):</strong> For enhanced reading features, install KOReader from its official source:
      <br />
      <a href="https://github.com/koreader/koreader" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://github.com/koreader/koreader</a>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Safety Tips</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Backup your important files before starting</li>
    <li>Do not disconnect or power off your Kindle during jailbreak</li>
    <li>Use only verified jailbreak files and sources</li>
    <li>Keep in mind that Amazon firmware updates can remove the jailbreak</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Further Resources</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.mobileread.com/forums/forumdisplay.php?f=142" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MobileRead Kindle Jailbreak Forum</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLkindleyouneed" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">YouTube Tutorials Playlist</a></li>
  </ul>
</SplitLayout>
